<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-28T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-28T05:00:00-05:00" n="400" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">365D.1163/25: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                            Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-28T13:00:00+03:00">December 28, 1936—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>700. Department’s 406, December 22, 6 p.m.<note n="80" xml:id="d400fn80">Not printed.</note> I am making inquiries of
                                authorities regarding the properties<note n="81" xml:id="d400fn81">Properties of the American (United Presbyterian)
                                    Mission.</note> at Sayo and also at Gore.</p>
                            <p>I understand that property of Seventh Day Adventists at Debra Tabor
                                and Ghimbi and property of Sudan Interior Mission at Debra Markos
                                have been occupied by the Italian military. No American citizens any
                                of these places.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>